[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix transpose .
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 3 2 matrix transpose .
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix transpose .
[ 7 ] 1 1 matrix transpose .
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix transpose transpose .

clear
\ reshape successes
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix 3 2 reshape .
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix 6 1 reshape .
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix 1 6 reshape .
[ 7 ] 1 1 matrix 1 1 reshape .
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 ] 4 2 matrix 2 4 reshape .
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 ] 4 2 matrix 8 1 reshape .

\ flatten successes
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix flatten .
[ 1 2 3 ] 1 3 matrix flatten .
3 identity-matrix flatten .

\ round-trip: flatten then reshape back
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix flatten 2 3 reshape .

\ reshape failures
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix 2 2 reshape
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix "x" 6 reshape
1 2 3 2 3 reshape

\ negative dims rejected (M4) — -2 * -2 == 4 would pass an int-only equality check
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 1 4 matrix -2 -2 reshape
\ element count overflows int (M4)
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 1 4 matrix 100000 100000 reshape

clear
\ oversized dimensions are rejected rather than silently overflowing int
100000 100000 0-matrix
1000000000 1000000000 0-matrix

\ negative dimensions still rejected
-1 3 0-matrix
3 -1 0-matrix

\ a large-but-valid matrix still constructs; dim reports its shape
100 100 0-matrix dim . .

\ ordinary small matrix is unaffected
2 3 0-matrix dim . .

\ size reports the element count (rows * columns) — the matrix analog of array/set size
cr
2 3 0-matrix size . cr                  \ 6
100 100 0-matrix size . cr              \ 10000
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 1 6 matrix size . cr    \ 6   row vector
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 6 1 matrix size . cr    \ 6   column vector
1 1 0-matrix size . cr                  \ 1   single element

\ num-elements: rows times columns
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix num-elements . cr  \ 6
1 1 0-matrix num-elements . cr                \ 1

clear
\ matrix>array ( m -- arr ): the elements as an array in row-major order.
\ A dimensioned matrix yields one quantity per element; NaN becomes null.
[ 5 1 4 ] vector matrix>array . cr             \ [ 5 1 4 ]
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix matrix>array . cr       \ [ 1 2 3 4 ]  row-major
[ 1 2 3 ] 1 3 matrix matrix>array . cr         \ [ 1 2 3 ]    row shape, same array
[ 7 ] 1 1 matrix matrix>array . cr             \ [ 7 ]
[ ] vector matrix>array size . cr              \ 0
[ 10 20 ] vector m matrix>array . cr           \ [ 10 m 20 m ]
[ 10 20 ] vector m matrix>array 0 @i 5 m + . cr \ 15 m
[ 1 -1 4 ] vector sqrt matrix>array . cr       \ [ 1 null 2 ]  NaN element surfaces as null
[ 1 -1 ] vector sqrt s matrix>array . cr       \ [ 1 s null ]  dimensioned NaN is bare null
[ -1 ] vector s matrix>array 0 @i . cr         \ -1 s          negatives keep their unit

\ round-trip: matrix>array then vector rebuilds the column
[ 5 1 4 ] vector matrix>array vector transpose . cr   \ 5 1 4 as 1x3

\ errors
5 matrix>array                                 \ error: not a matrix
"x" matrix>array                               \ error: not a matrix
